abstract: That famous locally known as Jackson's Hollow, situated in the Seventh Ward, Brookly, is a strip of low land extending from Flushing-avenue southward to DeKalb-avenue, and bounded by Classon-avenue on the east, and Ryerson-street on the west. This, however, is not the extent of the peculiar settlement which has sprung up there, for the "city of shanties" extends over the whole length of what was the old Jackson farm, across Fulton-avenue.

abstract: SUDDEN DEATH OF AN OLD STEAMBOAT CAPTAIN.-About 9 o'clock Wednesday evening, as Mr. ABRAHAM HITCHCOCK, formerly commander of several North River steamboats, was passing up Hudsonstreet near Laight, he was suddenly seized with a fit, and fell to the sidewalk. abstract: Mr. Thomas L. Yonug, a member of the Palmetto regiment during the Mexican war, recently died at Winnesboro', South Carolina.
